This according to The World Food Programme (WFP) the world's largest humanitarian agency fighting hunger worldwide. 

In 2016, heads of states on the continent declared their intentions to make school feeding an area of priority. 

WFP however says although there is great political will, countries still need to do more to successfully implement school feeding schemes. For more on this issue here's WFP's Director of School Feeding, Carmen Burbano… --ChannelAfrica--